title:Creamy Garlic Pasta
ingredients:2 teaspoons olive oil//
4 garlic cloves, minced//
2 tablespoons butter//
3 cups chicken broth, or more as needed//
1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper//
1/4 teaspoon salt//
1/2 pound spaghetti//
1 cup grated Parmesan cheese//
3/4 cup heavy cream//
1 1/2 tablespoons dried parsley
instructions:Heat olive oil in a medium pan over medium heat.//
Add garlic and stir until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes.//
Add butter and stir constantly until melted.//
Pour in 3 cups chicken broth, add pepper and salt.//
Bring to a boil.//
Add spaghetti and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes.//
Add more chicken broth if pasta starts to stick to the pan.//
Add Parmesan cheese, cream, and parsley and mix until thoroughly combined.//
Serve immediately.